    <h4>A Negatively Charged Line</h4>
    <p>
      The inward directed field extends radially from the line of charge. The electric
      field shows a cylindrical symmetry about the axis of the line of charge.
      Compare this to the spherical symmetry of the field from a point charge.
    </p>
    <details>
      <summary>Mouse Interactions</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Click and drag with the left mouse button to rotate the model.</li>
        <li>Use the mouse wheel to zoom in and out.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Touch Interactions</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Swipe with a finger to rotate the model.</li>
        <li>Pinch with two fingers to zoom in and out.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>
